oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: J. L. Cox and Company
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: J. L. Cox and Company, Petros. There is a mule-drawn wagon filled with people in front of the building. They are on a dirt road next to a boardwalk. Sign says "We Buy Roots of All Kinds."
J.L. Cox (1860-1925) tombstone indicates that he was "Uncle" and "K of R"
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
